    comment: '<p>According to the <strong>box model</strong>, every element on the page is a rectangular box that may have <code>width</code>, <code>height</code>, <code>margin</code>, <code>padding</code> or <code>border</code>.</p>\n<p>The dimensions of such a box are calculated by summing the values of the above mentioned properties. To better understand the formula, consider this example:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-css">div{\n  width: 600px;\n  height: 200px;\n  border: 4px solid blue;\n  margin: 20px;\n  padding: 10px;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p><svg height="auto" viewBox="0 0 810 310" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" version="1.2" baseProfile="tiny"><desc>Created by HiQPdf</desc><g fill="none" stroke="#000" fill-rule="evenodd" stroke-linecap="square" stroke-linejoin="bevel"><path d="M8 8h800v300H8V8" fill="#596193" stroke="none"/><path d="M75 15h666v286H75V15" fill="#fff" stroke="none"/><g fill="#596193" font-size="26" font-family="&#x27;Roboto&#x27;,sans-serif"><text x="110" y="37">Margin</text><text x="140" y="65">Border</text><text x="170" y="100">Padding</text><text x="195" y="130">Content</text></g><g font-size="22" font-weight="300" font-family="&#x27;Roboto&#x27;,sans-serif"><text x="393" y="37">20</text><text x="400" y="65">4</text><text x="393" y="100">10</text><text x="78" y="165">20</text><text x="115" y="165">4</text><text x="138" y="165">10</text><text x="365" y="165">600Ã—200</text></g><path d="M75 15h3v3h-3v-3M738 15h3v3h-3v-3" fill="#000" stroke="none"/><path fill="none" d="M78 16.5h659" stroke-dasharray="9,9" stroke-dashoffset="7" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="butt" stroke-linejoin="miter" stroke-miterlimit="2"/><path d="M75 298h3v3h-3v-3M738 298h3v3h-3v-3" fill="#000" stroke="none"/><path fill="none" d="M78 299.5h659" stroke-dasharray="9,9" stroke-dashoffset="7" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="butt" stroke-linejoin="miter" stroke-miterlimit="2"/><path d="M75 15h3v3h-3v-3M75 298h3v3h-3v-3" fill="#000" stroke="none"/><path fill="none" d="